{
  "stem": "3855.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And your matura, which was the final exam at the end of the gymnasium, entitled you to go to university if you had good grades.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The education system at the time was such that parents would already decide at the age of 10 or 11, whether the child would study-- the boy in those days-- would study or not.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Because it was at that time that he would either go to a gymnasium or go to a [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Berufsschule, ?] which really means citizen school, which prepared the lad for a trade.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And so you can see how stratified both the education and society was, because it was up to the intellectual level of the parents to groom the child to pursue the higher education.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my parents tried their best to have me study medicine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They went so far as to send me to an uncle, who was a doctor, for four summers in a row, and also to a cousin, who was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I, somehow-- it didn't-- to use a colloquialism-- turn me on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I just felt engineering was my calling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I pretty much also in my-- in the school, I particularly excelled in the realistic subjects, rather than in Latin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at the time that I attended it, it was called Vienna Technische Hochschule, which literally translated means Viennese Technical High School.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hochschule has a different connotation in Europe than over here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a school of higher learning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Typically after the war, the Austrians changed their name to Viennese Technical University.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In order to overcome this, well, I wouldn't call it stigma, because after a year or two when you're out in the field, the school doesn't count anymore.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's what you're doing that counts.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That goes for magnet schools as well.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
